chart|BillboardAlternative|3|artist=Sigur Ros|rowheader=true|accessdate=30 May 2018}}\n|-\n{{album chart|BillboardRock|4|artist=Sigur Ros|rowheader=true|accessdate=30 May 2018}}\n|}\n{{col-2}}\n\n===Year-end charts===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Chart (2012)\n! scope=\"col\"| Position\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Belgian Albums (Ultratop Flanders)<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ultratop.be/nl/annual.asp?year=2012&cat=a |title=Jaaroverzichten 2012 \u2013 Albums |language=Dutch |publisher=Ultratop |accessdate=30 May 2018}}</ref>\n| 75\n|}\n{{col-end}}\n\n==Release history==\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Region\n! scope=\"col\"| Date\n! scope=\"col\"| Label\n! scope=\"col\"| {{abbr|Ref.|Reference}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Japan\n| 23 May 2012\n| rowspan=\"3\"| [[EMI]]\n| align=\"center\"| <ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.emimusic.jp/artist/sigurros/?id=60294 |title=\u30b7\u30ac\u30fc\u30fb\u30ed\u30b9 / \u30f4\u30a1\u30eb\u30bf\u30ea \uff5e\u9060\u3044\u9f13\u52d5 |trans-title=Sigur R\u00f3s / Valtari |website=[[EMI Music Japan]] |language=Japanese |accessdate=2 June 2012 |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20120802080821/http://www.emimusic.jp/artist/sigurros/?id=60294 |archivedate=2 August 2012}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Australia\n| rowspan=\"2\"| 25 May 2012\n| align=\"center\"| <ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.jbhifionline.com.au/music/alternative/valtari/664741 |title=Valtari \u2013 Sigur Ros |website=[[JB Hi-Fi]] |accessdate=2 June 2012}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Germany\n| align=\"center\"| <ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.emimusic.de/release/3252262,5099962355520/sigur-ros-valtari |title=Sigur Ros // Valtari |website=[[EMI|EMI Music Germany]] |language=German |accessdate=2 June 2012 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120904195426/http://www.emimusic.de/release/3252262,5099962355520/sigur-ros-valtari |archivedate=4 September 2012}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| United Kingdom\n| 28 May 2012\n| [[Parlophone]]\n| align=\"center\"| <ref>{{cite web |url=http://hmv.com/hmvweb/displayProductDetails.do?ctx=280;1;-1;-1;-1&sku=655136 |title=Sigur Ros: Valtari |website=[[HMV]] |accessdate=2 June 2012 |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20120712105812/http://hmv.com/hmvweb/displayProductDetails.do?ctx=280;1;-1;-1;-1&sku=655136 |archivedate=12 July 2012}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| United States\n| 29 May 2012\n| [[XL Recordings|XL]]\n| align=\"center\"| <ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.amazon.com/Valtari-Sigur-Ros/dp/B007OWG3LM |title=Valtari: Sigur R\u00f3s |website=[[Amazon (website)|Amazon]] (US) |accessdate=30 May 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Taiwan\n| 8 June 2012\n| [[Gold Typhoon]]\n| align=\"center\"| <ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.gold-typhoon.com.tw/music/album/5389 |title=Gold Typhoon \u91d1\u724c\u5927\u98a8 |website=[[Gold Typhoon]] |language=Chinese |accessdate=29 May 2012 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120705041657/http://www.gold-typhoon.com.tw/music/album/5389 |archivedate=5 July 2012}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n{{Sigur R\u00f3s}}\n\n[[Category:2012 albums]]\n[[Category:Parlophone albums]]\n[[Category:Sigur R\u00f3s albums]]\n", "text_old": "{{Distinguish|Waltari}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2012}}\n{{Infobox album\n| name       = Valtari\n| type       = studio\n| artist     = [[Sigur R\u00f3s]]\n| cover      = Sigur Ros - Valtari.jpg\n| released   = {{Start date|2012|05|23|df=yes}}\n| recorded   = 2009\u20132012\n| studio     = [[Sundlaugin]], Greenhouse Studios, [[Air Studios]]\n| genre      = {{hlist|[[Post-rock]]|[[ambient music|ambient]]|[[dream pop]]<ref name=\"popmatters\">{{cite web |last=Ezell |first=Brice |url=http://www.popmatters.com/pm/review/159007-sigur-ros-valtari/ |title=Sigur R\u00f3s: Valtari |website=[[PopMatters]] |date=30 May 2012 |accessdate=26 November 2012 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121105012728/http://www.popmatters.com/pm/review/159007-sigur-ros-valtari/ |archivedate=5 November 2012}}</ref>}}\n| length     = {{duration|m=54|s=36}}\n| label      = [[Parlophone]]\n| producer   = {{hlist|Sigur R\u00f3s|[[Alex Somers]]}}\n| prev_title = [[Me\u00f0 su\u00f0 \u00ed eyrum vi\u00f0 spilum endalaust]]\n| prev_year  = 2008\n| next_title = [[Kveikur]]\n| next_year  = 2013\n| misc       = {{Singles\n| name        = Valtari\n| type        = studio\n| single1     = [[Ekki m\u00fakk]]\n| single1date = 26 March 2012\n| single2     = [[Var\u00fa\u00f0]]\n| single2date = 21 August 2012\n}}\n}}\n\n'''''Valtari''''' ({{IPA-is|\u02c8val\u0325tar\u026a}}, ''[[Road roller|Roller]]'')<ref name=\"pitchfork 26\">{{cite web |url=http://pitchfork.com/news/45911-sigur-ros-announce-new-album/ |title=Sigur R\u00f3s Announce New Album |date=26 March 2012 |accessdate=26 March 2012 |work=[[Pitchfork Media]] |first=Jenn |last=Pelly}}</ref> is the sixth studio album by Icelandic [[post-rock]] band [[Sigur R\u00f3s]]. It was released on 23 May 2012 by [[Parlophone]]. The album was commercially successful, reaching number eight on the [[UK Albums Chart]] and seven on the [[Billboard 200|''Billboard'' 200]]. The album was met with positive reviews as well with [[Metacritic]], which assigns a [[standard score|normalised]] rating out of 100 to reviews from mainstream critics, the album received an [[weighted mean|average]] score of 74, based on 36 reviews, indicating \"generally favorable reviews\".\n\nTwo singles were released from the album, the first being for \"[[Ekki m\u00fakk]]\" released on 10-inch vinyl for [[Record Store Day]], and the second being for \"[[Var\u00fa\u00f0]]\", as a limited edition 10-inch vinyl to coincide with their 2012 summer tour. ''Valtari''{{'}}s album cover is by [[J\u00f3nsi]]'s sisters, Lilja and Inga Birgisd\u00f3ttir. Inga was also the baby on the cover art for [[Sigur R\u00f3s]]' debut album ''[[Von (album)|Von]]''.<ref name=\"facebook\">{{cite web|title=Wall Photos|url=https://www.facebook.com/sigurros/photos/a.468604884123.265909.6187954123/10150745592779124/|publisher=[[Facebook]]|accessdate=7 November 2017|author=Sigur R\u00f3s}}</ref> It is the last album to feature keyboardist Kjartan Sveinsson.\n\n==Background==\nIn the fall of 2008, after the release of their fifth studio album ''[[Me\u00f0 su\u00f0 \u00ed eyrum vi\u00f0 spilum endalaust]]'', the band embarked on a world tour supporting their newly released album. The band played as a four-piece without [[Amiina]] and the brass band, the first time the band had played as a four-piece in seven years. The tour started on 17 September 2008 in the United States, at the [[United Palace Theater]] in New York City, and finished with a concert in Reykjav\u00edk at [[Laugardalsh\u00f6ll]] on 23 November 2008. The majority of the tour was European with the exception of concerts in the United States, Australia, Canada and Japan. The band then went on a break, with their manager saying it they were on an indefinite hiatus, although J\u00f3nsi commented saying \"We'd been touring for so many years and we'd gotten tired so we took a break and the guys had babies.\"<ref name=\"disinterview\">http://drownedinsound.com/in_depth/4144849-it-actually-feels-like-coming-home-again-dis-meets-jonsi-from-sigur-ros</ref>  J\u00f3nsi released an album titled ''[[Riceboy Sleeps]]'' in 2009 with his partner [[Alex Somers]], and then released a solo album titled ''[[Go (J\u00f3nsi album)|Go]]'' the next year.\n\nIn August 2011, they announced the release of their new live double album ''[[Inni (album)|Inni]]'' to be released on 7 November 2011. The recording is of the last show before they announced their \"indefinite hiatus\" at the end of 2008. It was recorded over two nights at [[London]]'s [[Alexandra Palace]]. It was to be released as a DVD, on CD and vinyl. The film debuted at the [[Venice Film Festival]] on 3 September 2011.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sigur-ros.co.uk/2011/08/ |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2013-12-13 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121029061748/http://www.sigur-ros.co.uk/2011/08/ |archivedate=29 October 2012 }}</ref> The album was then released on 7 November to critical acclaim. Commercially, it reached number 45 on the [[UK Albums Chart]] and number 73 on the [[Billboard 200|''Billboard'' 200]].<ref name=\"officialcharts.com\">http://www.officialcharts.com/artist/8399/sigur-ros/</ref><ref>https://www.allmusic.com/album/valtari-mw0002344605</ref>\n\n==Recording==\nDespite being on a break, the band began recording for the album in March 2009 with [[Alex Somers]], with some of the songs dating from 2007. \"Dau\u00f0alogn\" and \"Var\u00f0eldur\" started being recorded during these sessions, except they began to \"slow everything down\".<ref name=\"disinterview\" /><ref>https://www.rollingstone.com/music/news/sigur-ros-georg-holm-on-their-new-album-and-long-break-20120602</ref> The band began to use a lot of their old music and add other parts to it, but said it was \"not inspiring\", so they scrapped it and began again.  However, \"[[Fj\u00f6gur p\u00edan\u00f3]]\"  was made from a loop of some old material, which they kept. On 28 May 2009, Sigur R\u00f3s announced that they had almost completed recording their latest album.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sigur-ros.co.uk/news/?p=1313 |title=New album near completion |publisher=sigur-ros.co.uk | date=28 May 2009 |accessdate=2009-05-29 }}</ref> The unnamed album was expected to be released sometime in 2010. However, the band later revealed that the recordings had been scrapped. In a 2010 interview, J\u00f3nsi confirmed \"We haven't got another album ready\", he said. \"It was just a rumour. We started to record something, but then we chucked it all away. So I think we are going to have to start it all again\".<ref name=\"Michaels\">{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2010/jan/28/sigur-ros-indefinite-hiatus |work=[[The Guardian]] |title=Sigur R\u00f3s on indefinite hiatus after scrapping new album |first=Sean |last=Michaels |date=28 January 2010 |accessdate=2010-05-23}}</ref> Without further word on the new album, Sigur R\u00f3s were rumoured to be on indefinite hiatus as of January 2010.<ref name=\"Michaels\" /> However, before taking the stage at Coachella in April 2010, J\u00f3nsi commented that Sigur R\u00f3s would be getting back to work that year: \"I'm gonna record some other stuff with Sigur R\u00f3s when I'm home\", between a series of shows during his solo tour in summer 2010.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.spinner.ca/2010/04/20/jonsi-birgisson-sigur-ros-hiatus/ |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121112032817/http://www.spinner.ca/2010/04/20/jonsi-birgisson-sigur-ros-hiatus/ |url-status=dead |title=Jonsi Birgisson Sheds Light on Sigur Ros Hiatus |first=Steve |last=Baltin |publisher=[[Spinner (website)|Spinner]] |date=20 April 2010 |archivedate=2012-11-12}}</ref> On 1 February 2011, J\u00f3nsi's official website announced that he would be back in the studio with the band over the spring.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://culturetechreview.blogspot.com/2011/02/sigur-ros-in-studio-for-new-2011-album.html |title=Sigur Ros in the studio for a new 2011 album |publisher=Culture & Technology Review |date=1 February 2011 |accessdate=2011-06-07}}</ref>\n\nH\u00f3lm also said of the album:\n\n<blockquote>\nI really can't remember why we started this record, I no longer know what we were trying to do back then. I do know session after session went pear-shaped, we lost focus and almost gave up... did give up for a while. But then something happened and form started to emerge, and now I can honestly say that it's the only Sigur R\u00f3s record I have listened to for pleasure in my own house after we've finished it.<ref>{{cite web|title=Sigur R\u00f3s Official Website|url=http://www.sigur-ros.co.uk/valtari/|accessdate=18 June 2012}}</ref>\n</blockquote>\n\n==Composition==\nBassist [[Georg H\u00f3lm]] described the album as having \"more electronic stuff than before\" but not being \"a dance album\", and the band described the album as \"an avalanche in slow motion.\"<ref>http://www.clashmusic.com/features/frozen-adjectives-sigur-ros</ref> The album opening track \"\u00c9g anda\" has been described to have \"reverb-heavy guitars chiming quietly before J\u00f3nsi's distinctive falsetto floats in over what sounds like an army of music boxes\".<ref name=\"BBCreview\">{{cite web |last=Wallace |first=Wyndham |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/music/reviews/4z8r |title=Review of Sigur R\u00f3s \u2013 Valtari |publisher=[[BBC Music]] |date=14 May 2012 |accessdate=29 May 2012}}</ref> \"Dau\u00f0alogn\" and \"Var\u00f0eldur\" were written as far back as 2009, with \"Var\u00f0eldur\" being a different version of the song \"L\u00fappulagi\u00f0\" from ''Inni''.<ref name=\"hasitleaked\">{{cite web|last=Lacerda|first=Gabriel|title=Sigur R\u00f3s : Valtari|url=http://hasitleaked.com/2012/sigur-ros-valtari/|website=[[Has It Leaked]]|accessdate=29 May 2012|date=25 March 2012}}</ref> The second track \"Ekki m\u00fakk\" was referred to as \"an unhurried assembly of vinyl crackle and fragile guitar.\" The title of the album means \"[[Road roller|Roller]]\" in English, which J\u00f3nsi said they chose because they \"just liked that word\", saying that \"it kind of fits with the album because it's big and slow and rolls over you slowly.\" He said that it was the working title of one songs, but was then changed as the title for a different song which now is the seventh track on the album. The track \"Valtari\" has been described as \"a layered, gorgeous nothing, lush with nuanced drift and harmonic sweetness.\"<ref name=\"rollingstonereview\">{{cite web |last=Hermes |first=Will |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/albumreviews/valtari-20120529 |title=Sigur Ros: Valtari |work=[[Rolling Stone]] |date=29 May 2012 |accessdate=29 May 2012}}</ref> \"Fj\u00f6gur p\u00edan\u00f3\" was made up of different parts of old material that wasn't used, and they put it on loop, hence \"Four Pianos\".<ref name=\"disinterview\" />\n\n==Release==\nOn 26 March 2012, the band announced the details of their sixth [[studio album]], along with the premier of their new track \"[[Ekki m\u00fakk]]\".<ref>http://www.sigur-ros.co.uk/news/2012/new-album-valtari-out-may-28th/</ref> In April, they released \"Ekki m\u00fakk\" as a single for [[Record Store Day]] 2012, releasing it on limited edition 10\" vinyl that plays inside out. Its B-side is an instrumental track titled \"Kvistur\".<ref>{{cite web|author=|url=http://www.sigur-ros.co.uk/valtari/record-store-day/ |title= celebrating record store day, april 21st |website=Sigur-Ros.co.uk|accessdate=29 May 2012}}</ref>  This B-side is also available as a pre-order bonus track.<ref name=\"sigur r\u00f3s - buy valtari\">{{cite web|url=http://www.sigur-ros.co.uk/valtari/preorder |title=sigur r\u00f3s - buy valtari |website=Sigur-Ros.co.uk |accessdate=29 May 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120513201929/http://www.sigur-ros.co.uk/valtari/preorder/ |archivedate=13 May 2012 }}</ref> It was released along with a double vinyl release of ''[[Hvarf/Heim]]''.<ref>http://www.sigur-ros.co.uk/news/2012/two-new-releases-on-record-store-day/</ref> The song \"Dau\u00f0alogn\" was premiered during the [[The Vampire Diaries (season 3)|third season]] finale of ''[[The Vampire Diaries]]'', aired 10 May 2012.<ref>{{cite web |last=Young |first=Alex |url=https://consequenceofsound.net/2012/05/video-sigur-ros-debuts-daudalogn-on-the-vampire-diaries/ |title=Sigur R\u00f3s debuts \"Dau\u00f0alogn\" on ''The Vampire Diaries'' |website=[[Consequence of Sound]] |date=11 May 2012 |accessdate=29 May 2012}}</ref> On 17 May, the official website streamed the album online, in an activity called ''Valtari Hour'' at 7 p.m. at time zones around the world, in advance of the album's release.<ref>{{cite web|last=Young|first=Alex|title=Sigur R\u00f3s launches 'Valtari Hour' worldwide listening party|url=https://consequenceofsound.net/2012/05/sigur-ros-launches-valtari-hour-worldwide-listening-party/|website=Consequence of Sound|accessdate=29 May 2012|date=14 May 2012}}</ref><ref name=\"valtarihour\">{{cite web|title=valtari hour \u2013 global listening party|url=https://sigur-ros.co.uk/news/2012/valtari-hour-global-listening-party/|website=Sigur-Ros.co.uk|accessdate=7 November 2017|date=15 May 2012}}</ref> On the same day, [[Zane Lowe]] premiered another brand new track from the album, \"\u00c9g anda\", on [[BBC Radio 1]].<ref name=\"zane\">{{cite web|last=Lowe|first=Zane|title=Hottest Record - Sigur Ros - Eg anda|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/blogs/zanelowe/2012/05/hottest_record_-_sigur_ros_-_e.html|website=[[BBC]]|accessdate=29 May 2012|date=17 May 2012}}</ref>\n\nOn 28 May, ''Valtari'' was released through [[Parlophone]] on CD, vinyl and as a digital download. The album debuted at number eight on the [[UK Albums Chart]], selling 11,136 copies in its first week.<ref>{{cite web |last=Jones |first=Alan |url=http://www.musicweek.com/news/read/official-charts-analysis-gary-barlow-lp-sells-40k/049099 |title=Official Charts Analysis: Gary Barlow LP sells 40k |work=[[Music Week]] |date=3 June 2012 |accessdate=30 May 2018 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120909211702/http://www.musicweek.com/news/read/official-charts-analysis-gary-barlow-lp-sells-40k/049099 |archivedate=9 September 2012}}</ref> In the United States, the album entered the [[Billboard 200|''Billboard'' 200]] at number seven with first-week sales of 26,000 copies, the band's first top ten entry and third best sales week.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/484092/john-mayers-no-1-for-second-week-on-billboard-200 |title=John Mayer's No. 1 for Second Week on Billboard 200 |work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |date=6 June 2012 |accessdate=24 March 2013}}</ref> By March 2013, the album had sold 74,000 copies in US.<ref>{{cite web |last=Schneider |first=Marc |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/1554290/sigur-ros-announce-new-album-kveikur |title=Sigur R\u00f3s Announce New Album 'Kveikur' |work=Billboard |date=22 March 2013 |accessdate=4 August 2017}}</ref> On 21 August, the song \"Var\u00fa\u00f0\" was released as single in a special limited edition 10-inch vinyl to coincide with their 2012 summer tour. It plays inside out, just like \"Ekki m\u00fakk\". Its B-side, \"Logn\", is also a pre-order bonus track.<ref name=\"sigur r\u00f3s - buy valtari\" /><ref>{{cite web|author=|url=http://www.discogs.com/Sigur-R%C3%B3s-Var%C3%BA%C3%B0/release/3789714 |title= Sigur R\u00f3s \u2013 Var\u00fa\u00f0 |website=[[Discogs]]| accessdate=31 August 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author=|url=http://xlrecordings.com/releases/21650|title=Sigur R\u00f3s Var\u00fa\u00f0|website=[[XL Recordings]]|accessdate=31 August 2012}}{{Dead link|date=July 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n\n==The Valtari Mystery Film Experiment==\nThe ''Valtari Mystery Film Experiment'' was that Sigur R\u00f3s had given a dozen film makers the same budget and asked them to create whatever comes into their head when they listen to songs from the band's forthcoming album. The idea is to abandon the usual approval process from Sigur R\u00f3s, and allow film makers utmost creative freedom.<ref name=\"valtarivideos\">{{cite web|author=|url=http://sigur-ros.co.uk/valtari/videos/ |title= the valtari mystery film experiment |website=Sigur-Ros.co.uk |accessdate=29 May 2012}}</ref> Among the twelve filmmakers working without brief to a chosen song are [[Ramin Bahrani]], [[Alma Har'el]], [[John Cameron Mitchell]] and [[Ryan McGinley]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Sigur R\u00f3s launch 'Valtari' mystery film experiment today|url=http://www.music-news.com/ShowNews.asp?nItemID=52216|website=Music-News.com|accessdate=29 May 2012|date=21 May 2012}}</ref> The videos were premiered from 21 May to 6 December 2012.<ref name=\"valtarivideos\" /> The twelfth film, chosen by the band was the overall winner of the Valtari Film Competition, released on 15 October, called \"Skinned\" and features \"Fj\u00f6gur P\u00edan\u00f3\". It was directed by Anafelle Liu, Dio Lau and Ken Ngan.<ref name=\"valtarivideos\" />\n\nSigur R\u00f3s said:<ref name=\"everguide\">{{cite web|last=Fioritti|first=Bianca|url=http://everguide.com.au/music/gigs-and-festivals/news/sigur-ros-launch-valtari-film-project.aspx|title=Sigur Ros Launch Valtari Film Project|website=Everguide|date=22 May 2012|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131213193925/http://everguide.com.au/music/gigs-and-festivals/news/sigur-ros-launch-valtari-film-project.aspx|archivedate=13 December 2013}}</ref><ref name=\"Xu\">{{cite web|last=Xu|first=Johnnie|url=http://www.johnniexu.com/blog/93|title=Sigur R\u00f3s \u2013 Valtari|website=JohnnieXu.com|language=Chinese|date=24 May 2012|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121229043716/http://www.johnniexu.com/blog/93|archivedate=29 December 2012}}</ref>\n<blockquote>\n\"We never meant our music to come with a pre-programmed emotional response. We don't want to tell anyone how to feel and what to take from it. With the films, we have literally no idea what the directors are going to come back with. None of them know what the others are doing, so hopefully it could be interesting\"\n</blockquote>\n\n==Critical reception==\n{{Album reviews\n| MC = 74/100<ref name=\"MC\">{{Metacritic album |id=valtari|accessdate=2014-12-26}}</ref>\n| rev1 = [[AllMusic]] \n| rev1Score = {{Rating|4|5}}<ref name=\"allmusic\"/>\n| rev2 = ''[[The A.V. Club]]''\n| rev2Score = A\u2212<ref name=\"avclub\"/>\n| rev3 = [[BBC Music]]\n| rev3Score = Positive<ref name=\"BBCreview\"/>\n| rev4 = ''[[Drowned in Sound]]''\n| rev4Score = 8/10<ref name=\"DiS\"/>\n| rev5 = ''[[NME]]''\n| rev5Score = 7/10<ref name=\"NME\"/>\n| rev6 = ''[[The Observer]]''\n| rev6Score = {{Rating|3|5}}<ref>{{cite web |last=Hoby |first=Hermion |url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2012/may/27/sigur-ros-valtari-review |title=Sigur R\u00f3s: Valtari \u2013 review |work=[[The Observer]] |date=26 May 2012 |accessdate=29 May 2012}}</ref>\n| rev7 = ''[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]''\n| rev7Score = 6.1/10<ref name=\"pitchfork\"/>\n| rev8 = ''[[PopMatters]]''\n| rev8Score = 7/10<ref name=\"popmatters\"/>\n| rev9 = ''[[Rolling Stone]]''\n| rev9Score = {{Rating|3.5|5}}<ref name=\"rollingstonereview\"/>\n| rev10 = ''[[Slant Magazine]]''\n| rev10Score = {{Rating|4|5}}<ref>{{cite web |last=Liedel |first=Kevin |url=https://www.slantmagazine.com/music/review/sigur-ros-valtari |title=Sigur R\u00f3s: Valtari |website=[[Slant Magazine]] |date=26 May 2012 |accessdate=30 May 2018}}</ref>\n}}\n''Valtari'' received generally positive reviews from music critics. At [[Metacritic]], which assigns a [[standard score|normalized]] rating out of 100 to reviews from mainstream publications, the album received an [[weighted arithmetic mean|average]] score of 74, based on 36 reviews.<ref name=\"MC\"/> [[AllMusic]] writer Tim Sendra said the album was \"filled with giant washes of sound bathed in reverb, echoing keyboards, smears of strings, and massed backing vocals, the album ebbs and flows from giant crescendos to heartbreakingly intimate moments with Jonsi's otherworldly voice riding the waves like a mythical dolphin\", ending the review saying, \"On the surface, Valtari may seem like a step back for the band, but instead of just retreading the past, the album is one of their best; a refined display of their musical power with breathtaking dynamics and enough emotion to flood an ocean.\"<ref name=\"allmusic\">{{cite web |last=Sendra |first=Tim |url=https://www.allmusic.com/album/valtari-mw0002344605 |title=Valtari \u2013 Sigur R\u00f3s |website=[[AllMusic]] |accessdate=2 June 2012}}</ref> ''[[The A.V. Club]]'' said that \"the relative restraint on the single 'Ekki M\u00fakk' and other more straightforward songs like 'Var\u00fa\u00f0' and 'Rembihn\u00fatur' is a welcome shift for the group, ditching the bigger-is-better grandiloquence and predictable arcs of Sigur R\u00f3s' recent work.\"<ref name=\"avclub\">{{cite web |last=Plagenhoef |first=Scott |url=https://music.avclub.com/sigur-ros-valtari-1798172960 |title=Sigur R\u00f3s: Valtari |work=[[The A.V. Club]] |date=29 May 2012 |accessdate=30 May 2018}}</ref> [[BBC Music]] writer Wyndham Wallace said that \"much of the album sounds like it's made up of what would, in previous years, have only qualified as the introductions to songs. Opening track \"\u00c9g anda\" takes an age to get underway, reverb-heavy guitars chiming quietly before J\u00f3nsi's distinctive falsetto floats in over what sounds like an army of music boxes, and, though Rembihn\u00fatur lifts off towards its end in a familiar fashion, drums are largely limited to distorted electronic pulses and there are none of the earth-scorching effects that have previously characterised similar moments,\" and that \"for those more patient, however, the album represents calm after a storm, and highlights how Sigur R\u00f3s remain as eager to challenge themselves as their audience.\"<ref name=\"BBCreview\"/>\n\n''[[Drowned in Sound]]'' stated that \"this is not an album of easy melodies, of playful riffs and crowd-pleasing moments. Indeed, it seems not for the crowd at all: as background music this fades away, shrinking into a still corner away from the noise.\" They later said that \"''Valtari'' seems rather brave: across a runtime of nearly an hour there's little effort to hold our attention, to vary the tone or venture anywhere, anywhere near mainstream appeal. And sure, huge swathes of this may run the risk of passing by unnoticed, of blurring into a single reverbed note, but that's our responsibility, and quite frankly our loss\", ending the review saying \"''Valtari'' might not be a huge digression for the band but that doesn't matter: this is quietly, entrancingly and thoroughly sublime.\"<ref name=\"DiS\">{{cite web |last=Cottingham |first=Christian |url=http://drownedinsound.com/releases/17026/reviews/4145013 |title=Sigur R\u00f3s \u2013 Valtari |website=[[Drowned in Sound]] |date=28 May 2012 |accessdate=29 May 2012}}</ref> ''[[NME]]'', however, wrote that \"this record will maintain their fan base, but it won't attract a new one\".<ref name=\"NME\">{{cite web |last=Dando |first=Kristian |url=http://www.nme.com/reviews/sigur-ros/13224 |title=Sigur Ros \u2013 'Valtari' |work=[[NME]] |date=25 May 2012 |accessdate=30 May 2012 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120601083602/http://www.nme.com/reviews/sigur-ros/13224 |archivedate=1 June 2012}}</ref> ''[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]'' was not so positive either, stating, \"The problem isn't that ''Valtari'' aspires to beauty, even if it's a commonplace, celestial understanding of it. Sigur R\u00f3s have proven they can make indelible music that's pretty and unpredictable, pretty and melodic, pretty and unnerving, pretty and inspiring. Valtari wants to be pretty and that's it.\"<ref name=\"pitchfork\">{{cite web |last=Cohen |first=Ian |url=https://pitchfork.com/reviews/albums/16628-sigur-ros-valtari/ |title=Sigur R\u00f3s: Valtari |website=[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]] |date=30 May 2012 |accessdate=30 May 2012}}</ref> ''[[Rolling Stone]]'' said that \"J\u00f3nsi's exquisite vocals evoke prayers or lullabies, while pecked-out piano melodies play amid dulcimer tones, sonar burps, elf choirs.\"<ref name=\"rollingstonereview\"/>\n\n==Track listing==\n{{Track listing\n| total_length = 54:36\n| all_writing = [[Sigur R\u00f3s]]\n| extra_column = English translation{{ref|a|[a]}}\n| title1 = \u00c9g anda\n| extra1 = \"I Breathe\"\n| length1 = 6:15\n| title2 = [[Ekki m\u00fakk]]\n| extra2 = \"Not a Sound\"\n| length2 = 7:45\n| title3 = [[Var\u00fa\u00f0]]\n| extra3 = \"Caution\"\n| length3 = 6:37\n| title4 = Rembihn\u00fatur\n| extra4 = \"Tight Knot\"\n| length4 = 5:05\n| title5 = Dau\u00f0alogn\n| extra5 = \"Dead Calm\"\n| length5 = 6:37\n| title6 = Var\u00f0eldur\n| extra6 = \"Campfire\"\n| length6 = 6:08\n| title7 = Valtari\n| extra7 = \"Roller\"\n| length7 = 8:19\n| title8 = [[Fj\u00f6gur p\u00edan\u00f3]]\n| extra8 = \"Four Pianos\"\n| length8 = 7:50\n}}\n{{Track listing\n| total_length = 68:20\n| collapsed = yes\n| headline = Pre-order bonus tracks\n| extra_column = English translation{{ref|a|[a]}}\n| title9 = Logn\n| extra9 = \"Calm\"\n| length9 = 8:14\n| title10 = Kvistur\n| extra10 = \"Branch\"\n| length10 = 5:30\n}}\n* {{sup|{{note|a|a}}}} English translations not official.\n\n==Personnel==\n'''Sigur R\u00f3s'''\n* [[J\u00f3nsi|J\u00f3n \u00de\u00f3r \"J\u00f3nsi\" Birgisson]]\n* [[Georg H\u00f3lm|Georg \"Goggi\" H\u00f3lm]]\n* [[Kjartan Sveinsson|Kjartan \"Kjarri\" Sveinsson]]\n* [[Orri P\u00e1ll D\u00fdrason]]\n\n'''Additional musicians'''\n* [[Amiina]] ''(Hildur \u00c1rs\u00e6lsd\u00f3ttir, Edda R\u00fan \u00d3lafsd\u00f3ttir, Maria Huld Markan Sigf\u00fasd\u00f3ttir, S\u00f3lr\u00fan Sumarli\u00f0ad\u00f3ttir)'' \u2013 strings and string arrangements (except for \"Var\u00fa\u00f0\")\n* Una Sveinbjarnard\u00f3ttir, Palina Arnad\u00f3ttir, Borunn \u00d3sk Marinosd\u00f3ttir, Margret Arnad\u00f3ttir, Boigar Magnason \u2013 strings on \"Var\u00fa\u00f0\"\n*Holmfridur Benediktsd\u00f3ttir, Hildur F. Havarjurd\u00f3ttir, Bjorg Gardursd\u00f3ttir, Sulka B. Svanhuitard\u00f3ttir, Brynhildur Melot, Hera Eriksd\u00f3ttir - backing vocals on \"Var\u00fa\u00f0\"\n*[[Dan\u00edel Bjarnason]] \u2013 string arrangements on \"Var\u00fa\u00f0\"\n*[[The Sixteen]] \u2013 [[choir]] on \"Dau\u00f0alogn\" and \"Var\u00f0eldur\"\n*Eamonn Dougan \u2013 choral direction on \"Dau\u00f0alogn\" and \"Var\u00f0eldur\"\n\n==Charts==\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n\n===Weekly charts===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Chart (2012)\n! scope=\"col\"| Peak<br>position\n|-\n{{album chart|Australia|14|artist=Sigur R\u00f3s|album=Valtari|rowheader=true|accessdate=4 June 2012}}\n|-\n{{a